task_description: Facing the building to your South-East (approx. 147°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to see the full height of the building to estimate it, so I will start by looking up to find the roof.
My heading was reset to 0° North, so I need to rotate back to face the target building at 147° South-East before I can continue my assessment.
I have reoriented myself to face the building at 147°; now I will look up again to see the top of the building.
My heading was reset to 0° North again; I need to rotate back to 147° South-East while maintaining my upward pitch to view the top of the building.
I have reoriented to face the building at 147° again; I will now look up to see the top of the building and hopefully the system will retain my heading this time.
The system keeps resetting my heading to 0° North; I will rotate back to 147° South-East and also look down to see the base of the building to get a full view for estimation.
I have now seen the base of the building; I will look up by 60 degrees to scan from the bottom to the top and get a full view of its height.

The heading was reset again, but I can now see the top of the building's spire; having previously viewed the base, I can estimate the building has about 6 floors plus a large roof and spire, leading to an estimate of around 30 meters.
